      • isOn

        boolean isOn()
        Is this variation currently online.

        Offline variations are treated specially:

        1. A session traversing this variation will always see control experience.
        2. If the session already has an entry for this variation in its targeting tracker, the entry will be ignored, but not discarded. If not, no entries will be added to the user’s targeting tracker.
        3. No trace events will be logged for this variation.
        Returns:
        true if the test is online, false if not.
        Since:
        0.5

      • isSerialWith

        default boolean isSerialWith(Variation other)
        Is this variation serial with a given variation. Two variations are serial when there does not exist a state instrumented by both. Serial variations can be targeted independently without any additional considerations.
        Parameters:
        other -
        Returns:
        Since:
        0.5

      • isConcurrentWith

        boolean isConcurrentWith(Variation other)
        Is this variation concurrent with a given variation. This is equivalent to !isSerialWith(other). Concurrent variations cannot be targeted independently, unless they are declared to be conjointly concurrent and the host application has provided hybrid state variants.
        Parameters:
        other -
        Returns:
        Since:
        0.5
